INTELLIPLANT AI TECHNICAL MANUAL — FLOWSERVE P-401 CENTRIFUGAL PUMP
Document Ref: TM-P401-001 | Version: v3.2 | Asset Code: P-401 | Location: Plant A

1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW & SPECIFICATIONS
The P-401 Centrifugal Pump is a heavy-duty single-stage end-suction pump manufactured by Flowserve, designed for continuous hydrocarbon fluid transport in Plant A.
- Nominal Flow Rate: 450 m³/h
- Max Head: 85 meters
- Motor Power: 15 kW (3-Phase 415V, 50Hz)
- Impeller Diameter: 315 mm (Tolerance: ±0.05 mm)
- Mechanical Seal Type: Double Cartridge Seal with API Plan 11/52 Flushing System
- Operating Temperature Limit: -20°C to 180°C

2. LUBRICATION & MAINTENANCE INTERVALS
- Primary Lubricant: Mobilith SHC 220 Synthetic Grease
- Relubrication Interval: 1,400 Operating Hours (Reduced from 2,000h per RCA-2024-118 recommendations).
- Grease Quantity per Bearing: 45 grams
- Oil Reservoir Capacity: 2.5 Liters (Shell Tellus S2 MX 68)
- Oil Sampling & Spectrometric Analysis: Every 90 Days

3. VIBRATION THRESHOLDS & CONDITION MONITORING
Vibration telemetry is continuously fed into the IntelliPlant AI Analytics module.
- Normal Operating Level: < 2.5 mm/s RMS
- Warning Level (Alert): 4.2 mm/s RMS — Requires inspection scheduling within 48 hours.
- Trip / Alarm Level: 7.1 mm/s RMS — Immediate emergency shutdown protocol.
- Bearing Starvation Symptom: High-frequency acceleration peaks (10 kHz - 20 kHz peak-value spectrum) accompanied by a 12°C temperature rise above ambient baseline.

4. TROUBLESHOOTING & REPAIR PROCEDURES
Symptom: Excessive vibration > 4.2 mm/s and temperature rise.
Step 1: Check lube reservoir level and inspect sight glass for discoloration or water contamination.
Step 2: Perform laser alignment verification using Fixturlaser NXA (radial offset < 0.03 mm, angular tilt < 0.05°).
Step 3: If bearing starvation is suspected, inject 45g Mobilith SHC 220 grease and monitor temperature decay for 30 minutes.
Step 4: Log all findings in the Maintenance Intelligence module under Work Order WO-101.